commit.title: Fixes #8369 (Not_found in printing message about an unresolved subevar).
commit.message:
Fixes #8369 (Not_found in printing message about an unresolved subevar).

We were trying to print the name of a resolved evar. As a fix, we used
the name of the evar if it has a known user name and an anonymous
"subterm" expression if it has no known user name.

Maybe should we not even try to use the original name as this name may
have been "donated" to another (unresolved) evar in situations of
instantiations which do not "essentially" change the view we have at
the evar (i.e. "intro", "assert")?
